Macbeth was a war hero not long ago, but now he’s hiring lackeys to murder his ex-best-pal And although

Macbeth’s soliloquy uses imagery of a “fruitless crown” and “barren sceptre”. The double
meaning of “fruitless” (meaning both ‘futile’ and ‘bearing no fruit’) hints that he feels his
reign is worthless since he has no child to be his heir. Shakespeare uses the semantic
field of agriculture to contrast Macbeth with Duncan, who helps his subjects “grow”.
